<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="84.[192,1440,451,540]" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,324,451,475]" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon and Hanley" authorityYear="2017" box="[331,501,451,475]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Prodilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kristi">
<emphasis box="[331,501,451,475]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">Prodilis kristi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by its large size, blue elytron, lateral pronotal margin widely yellow, densely punctured dorsal surface, and prosternal base medially emarginate. This species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon &amp; Hanley" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Prodilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sandy">
<emphasis box="[1415,1433,484,507]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[192,264,515,539]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">sandy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be conspecific, see remarks under the latter species.
</paragraph>
